http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Wagon-derails/article14596143.ece

A goods wagon derailed near the Korukkupettai railway station on Sunday evening.Southern Railway sources said a goods train with 12 wagons carrying ballast was being shunted near the Korukkupettai station when one of them jumped off the rails around 5 p.m. It was re-railed at 6.30 p.m. There was no disruption of traffic of long-distance express or mail trains on the main lines, the sources said, adding that a few electrical multiple unit services from Chennai Beach were delayed slightly.